  <title>XS0675</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>XS0675</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Warning XS0675</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Bitwise-or operator used on a sign-extended operand; consider casting to a smaller unsigned type first</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The compiler implicitly widened and sign-extended a variable, and then used the resulting value in a bitwise OR operation. This can result in unexpected behavior.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The following sample generates XS0675:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box">// XS0675.prg  <br/>// compile with: /W:3  <br/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
</topic>
